        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 14 at 2:54AM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 254 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Roslyn, or 9 miles northwest of Enemy Swim Housing, moving northeast
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sisseton, Agency Village, Enemy Swim Housing, Roslyn, Peever, Eden,
Grenville, Lake City, Finley Heights Housing, Buffalo Lakes, Clear
Lake Rec Area, Piyas Lake, Waubay Wildlife Rec Area, Enemy Swim Lake,
Fort Sisseton State Park, Campbell Slough, Red Iron Housing, Pickerel
Lake Rec Area, Long Hollow Housing, and Opitz Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
